title: NSW great white shark heads north to Sunshine Coast for school holidays
text: While northern New South Wales beachgoers have been shocked by a year of heightened shark activity and attacks, Queensland beaches have been relatively calm, but a new tracking program has shown the seas off Queensland's beautiful beaches may not be as innocuous as they seem. ...
